<abstract><t>OSPFv2 requires functional extension beyond what can readily be done with the fixed-format Link State Advertisements (LSAs) as described in RFC 2323.  This document defines OSPF opaque LSAs based on Type- Length-Value (TLV) tuples that can be used to associate additional attributes with advertised prefixes or links.  The OSPF opaque LSAs are optional and fully backward compatible.</t></abstract>

